<TEXT>
michael dukakis is counting on making himself 
more familiar and likable through a trio of tv ads that feature the 
massachusetts governor speaking directly to viewers about their 
families and the nation 
the starkly simple ads show dukakis in his shirt sleeves on a 
couch and in a suit standing behind a chair he speaks of family 
concerns in two spots of the countrys slipping international 
economic status in the third 
theyre one more attempt to give the american people a chance 
to know who mike dukakis is said dukakis spokeswoman lorraine 
voles obviously we feel if they know who he is theyre going to 
like him 
voles said the ads which began friday were the only ones 
scheduled to run nationally through the weekend 
though the consensus is that republican george bush won the 
thursday night debate between the two presidential rivals voles 
said the event gave dukakis a chance to talk positively about his 
message in front of the american people 
the ads are a good followup to the debate she said they 
lay out more of who mike dukakis really is and where he wants to 
take this country 
the bush campaign also unveiled a new national television spot 
at the end of the week keyed to the nuclear arms reduction treaty 
president reagan signed with soviet leader mikhail s gorbachev 
the ad shows pictures of americans riding a tractor reading on 
a porch and eating dinner as a narrator discusses the day the 
soviets began destroying missiles under the new treaty 
and though most americans were unaware of the significance of 
the moment or realized it was george bush who led the way someday 
their grandchildren will the narrator concludes over a shot of 
bush with one of his grandchildren in a swing 
the new dukakis ads mark a departure from the campaigns other 
efforts which have included direct hits at bush and a string of 
controversial highly polished ads seeking to depict bush as a 
packaged candidate with no substance 
in one spot dukakis discusses the daily challenge of 
finding day care the threat of drugs and the need for twoearner 
households to stay even 
the republicans say that the futures never been brighter 
dukakis says but if i were a young father today id want to 
know that my government wasnt blind to the changes in my life 
thats not a democratic concern its not a republican concern 
thats a fathers concern 
in a second ad dukakis says the nation isnt leading the world 
anymore in education or international trade and instead of 
people owing us we owe them 
how did we let this happen he asks well i think instead 
of looking for new answers we went with the old ones instead of 
doing the right thing we began doing the easy thing and now were 
in danger of falling behind im not going to let that happen 
i believe the best america is yet to come 
the third ad is a 30second version of the family spot 
with the introduction of its backtobasics approach the 
campaign pulled off the air after only one day the latest in its 
packaging of george bush series the ads six in all feature a 
group of actors playing cynical bush handlers who mock different 
aspects of bushs record as they try to figure out ways to make him 
palatable to voters 
voles said the removal of the latest packaging ad was not a 
response to complaints about the series which many commentators 
have branded elitist and obscure you may very well be seeing 
that ad along with the other packaging ads again she said 
in addition an official said another new ad will begin airing 
in texas with lloyd bentsen delivering a testimonial to dukakis 
and asking supporters in his home state to rally behind the 
democratic ticket 
dukakis also plans to make extensive use of offers to appear on 
television news programs including abcs nightline campaign 
aides said 
