emperor hirohito was in stable condition today 
after experiencing a high temperature the previous day but his 
internal bleeding continued officials said 
the 87yearold emperors condition is leveling off kenji 
maeda spokesman for the imperial household agency told reporters 
quoting akira takagi the chief court physician maeda added 
that doctors were not planning to give hirohito additional blood 
transfusions despite signs of slight bleeding sometime between 
friday night and saturday morning 
maeda said the emperors temperature fell to 995 compared to 
1006 friday night hirohitos normal temperature is believed to be 
959 
the emperors temperature has constantly hovered around 
968986 and occasionally peaked over 1004 since he fell ill 
after vomiting blood sept 19 from internal hemorrhaging 
physicians have attributed the stubborn fever to an inflammation 
of the bile duct and bleeding from the upper duodenum and are 
worried about the possible recurrence of a large amount of blood 
discharge the local media have said 
palace officials have also expressed worry over hirohitos 
worsening jaundice and the worlds longestreigning monarch living 
has occasionally complained of fatigue according to the news 
reports 
japans postworld war ii constitution reduced the emperors 
role from living god to the symbol of state and of the unity of 
the people and allows him only ceremonial duties 
