<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap thousands of chanting youths 
marched for a second day near a burnedout church to protest 
reports that roman catholic officials ordered a radical priest out 
of haiti 
soldiers fired in the air to disperse some of the demonstrators 
who burned tires across the road leading to the citys airport the 
youths set the fires after rumors spread that rev jean bertrand 
aristide was about to leave the country radio stations said 
bishop guire poulard bishop of the southern town of jacmel 
said on the roman catholic churchs radio soleil that the rumor of 
aristides imminent departure was unfounded 
about 6000 demonstrators marched for three hours friday from 
the ruins of st jean bosco church where aristide was pastor to 
the headquarters of the haitian bishops conference in pacot the 
same 2mile route was traced by about 6000 protesters thursday 
the bishops conference on sunday condemned the radical wing of 
the church headed by aristide for allegedly preaching violence 
and class warfare 
the youths enthusiastic but orderly chanted slogans calling on 
the church to change its mind and allow aristide to remain 
aristide one of the most popular figures in haiti was an 
outspoken critic of lt gen henri namphys regime namphy was 
ousted by rankandfile soldiers in a coup sept 17 and replaced by 
lt gen prosper avril 
on sept 11 aristide was saying mass at his st jean bosco 
church when thugs attacked parishioners killing at least 12 
wounding 70 and burning down the church the soldiers that led the 
coup cited that massacre and other statesponsored violence as 
reasons for seizing power 
