<DOCNO> AP881015-0035 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
fifty years after the first jews fled nazi 
europe for shanghai the refugees from around the world gathered to 
recall nights in crowded warehouses and life in the steamy port 
that was their haven 
its been an electrifying experience ive met so many people 
i havent seen in all these years said norman shelton 61 who 
left berlin for shanghai in april 1939 and now lives in orlando 
fla 
shelton was among about 18000 jewish refugees who fled germany 
austria and poland for shanghai in 1938 and 1939 the chinese port 
was then the only place in the world where escaping jews could 
settle without visas 
most remained there until 1948 
about 150 of the group who call themselves the 
shanghailanders gathered this week for a fourday reunion 
that ended friday it was held in israel to coincide with the 
countrys 40th anniversary celebrations 
reunions also were held in 1980 in los angeles and in 1985 in 
new york but many of those who came to israel missed the earlier 
gatherings they sang japanese nursery rhymes traded yellowed 
photographs of soccer games played in the teeming shanghai streets 
and renewed friendships 
you cant believe the excitement i met someone here that i 
slept alongside for four years in the same dormitory and havent 
seen since said frankfurtborn manfred konig of new york 
some of their more famous comrades including artist peter max 
and extreasury secretary michael blumenthal were absent 
the journey to china from europe was a perilous odyssey that 
took a month often through siberia by rail and then by freighter 
ship to shanghai 
the refugees left with just 10 marks about 4 in their pockets 
and carried naziissued passports stamped with a large red j 
for jew and the words for exit only 
the twoyear exodus to shanghai began after the crystal 
night nov 9 1938 when naziled rioters attacked jewish homes 
and businesses in germany and austria and set dozens of synagogues 
ablaze 
the attack marked the start of adolf hitlers slaughter of 6 
million jews 
sheltons father was among the 30000 jews arrested and sent to 
concentration camps at dachau and buchenwald on crystal night 
we soon discovered the only way to get my dad out was to go to 
the nazis with a oneway ticket out of germany shelton said 
my mother was frantic she ran into the street and people told 
her about shanghai we got the money together and we were gone in 
three weeks 
shelton described his fathers shock as the family prepared to 
flee the first thing my dad did after getting out of that 
concentration camp was to pull out his world war i decorations and 
throw them into the toilet bowl 
curt pollack whose family fled berlin in january 1939 recalled 
the rampant disease and malnutrition that awaited the refugees in 
subtropical shanghai and left about 2000 dead 
these men were released from concentration camps straight onto 
the boat after 28 arduous days they arrived in the stifling heat 
of shanghai my father had dysentery within a week people were 
dying right and left he said 
germanborn claude spingarn was nine years old when his family 
arrived at shanghai in march 1939 
we were piled into this pickup truck and taken to a warehouse 
where about 100 people were sleeping in bedrolls on the floor 
rations were served from a soup kitchen my mother was in shock 
said spingarn of rochester ny 
when the pacific war broke out in 1942 the shanghai jews were 
confined by the occupying japanese to a 3squaremile ghetto in a 
warehouse district jobs were scarce and hunger widespread but 
pollack said the hardships forged a special closeness 
we formed a permanent bond i was born in germany and i live 
in los angeles but my most vivid memories are of shanghai he 
said 
pollack like many other shanghai jews has since returned to 
the teeming chinese port in 1980 and 1984 
i had the desire to go back and see the old neighborhood 
again he said some people go back to brooklyn to see if the 
old deli is still there for me shanghai is the closest thing i 
can come to reminiscing and going back 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

