<TEXT>
if you woke up bored dont go back to bed quite yet oct 16th 
has a better chance than most days of finding a significant niche 
in history and youd feel awful if you missed it 
the date has started and ended eras scrambled the balance of 
power and marched us off toward war or to the edge of it 
there are other days of historical coincidence that loom large 
of course 
there was july 4 and not just because of the independence 
said robert sellen professor of american history at georgia state 
university 
john adams and thomas jefferson died on july 4 exactly 50 years 
after the signing sellen noted and people marveled at this at 
the time these two old heroes of independence dying together 
it was seen as a symbol nobody was sure of what 
neither is anybody sure why all of these beginnings and endings 
fell on oct 16 
in 1793 queen marie antoinette whose extravagance and let 
them eat cake attitude toward the poor made her a symbol and 
cause of the french revolution went to the guillotine in paris it 
was the end of the old order and france would never be the same 
again with the stability of the continents monarchies in 
question neither would europe 
in 1815 napoleon bonaparte arrived at the island of saint 
helena off the west african coast where he was exiled after his 
loss to the british at waterloo the exile gave some finality 
again to the end of the napoleonic wars that shredded europe 
earlier he escaped from exile on elba off the coast of italy and 
nearly regained his power this time he stayed put and died on 
saint helena in 1821 
in 1846 a boston dentist william morton demonstrated the use 
of ether as an anesthetic during a jaw operation try to imagine 
medicine today without that first step 
in 1859 abolitionist john brown led his raid on the federal 
arsenal at harpers ferry va now wva in what was to have 
triggered a slave uprising it didnt and brown went to the 
gallows six weeks later the memory of brown and his raid became a 
rallying cry to turn out northern support for the war against the 
confederacy 
in 1916 margaret sanger opened the first birth control clinic 
in the united states on the revolutionary some said blasphemous 
contention that the poor should be able to control the size of 
their families she founded planned parenthood which has 
influenced the lives of millions 
in 1946 10 nazi war criminals who personified the worst of 
hitlers outrages were hanged in germany 
in 1962 the cuban missile crisis began with president kennedy 
ordering a blockade of cuba that brought the united states and the 
soviet union as close to nuclear war as they have ever been the 
soviets agreed to remove the missiles and kennedy lifted the 
blockade 
in 1964 china became the fifth member of the nuclear club 
exploding its first atomic bomb near sinkiang 
in 1970 anwar sadat who defied his moslem neighbors and was 
isolated by them for holding peace talks with israel was elected 
president of egypt his decision made the camp david peace talks 
possible 
in 1978 the college of cardinals snapped the 456yearold 
italian monopoly on the papacy by electing cardinal karol wojtyla 
of poland as pope john paul ii 
