president ronald reagans weekly address 
last month i had an unusual phone call from texas sen lloyd 
bentsen he asked me to play dan quayle and help him prepare for 
the vicepresidential debate i eagerly accepted i thought it 
would be fun 
however as i began to study up on sen quayle i realized that 
i was studying a controversial man a man who did not share the 
lives the needs and the hopes of many of my constituents in 
northeastern ohio a man who took every shortcut available who 
never struggled to make ends meet to make college costs or to pay 
his rent 
i had to wonder what it was about dan quayle that george bush 
liked i realized there have been a lot of those folks in george 
bushs career robert bork rita lavelle james watt and ed 
meese and never once did george bush question their judgment or 
their ability to serve its no wonder he picked a guy like dan 
quayle 
