<TEXT>
police divers on saturday recovered 
the bodies of two pennsylvania men from the st lawrence river and 
were searching for a third man after their boat sank friday night 
richard ruffner 36 of windeer pa and william evans 36 
drowned police said evans pennsylvania hometown was not 
immediately known 
keith schuyler 44 of muncy pa was missing and presumed 
drowned 
the trio set out in a 15foot boat to go fishing police said 
authorities said they believed high winds and rough water caused 
the vessel to sink late friday 
