<TEXT>
a 2yearold boy who climbed from his crib 
walked outside and fell into a canal was kept from drowning when 
his pajamas trapped air and kept his face bobbing above water 
his mother heard the screams and pulled albert joseph out with 
help from the family dog a mixed breed named lady who also jumped 
into the water said the boys grandmother mi dunn 
ms dunn said the boys mother patricia joseph was sleeping 
when the child woke up about 8 am friday 
he climbed out of the crib opened up the door and went out 
ms dunn said usually he comes to me 
albert joseph padded into the back yard which is bordered by an 
unfenced canal up to 15 feet deep and fell in 
his zippered pajamas trapped the air keeping his face above 
water said paramedic mark von stein 
he was very lucky there are very slim chances of something 
like this ever happening said von stein 
</TEXT>
