<TEXT>
uniformed men identifying 
themselves as soldiers took four young peasants from their homes 
tied them up shot them in the head and left their bodies laid out 
in a row relatives said saturday 
the relatives said the men who came to the village friday night 
identified their unit as the 1st army brigade and said they were 
just carrying out orders 
the allegations came only weeks after an incident in which 
soldiers allegedly massacred 10 peasants in the san vicente 
province the soldiers accused the peasants of collaborating with 
leftist guerrillas who are at war with the usbacked government 
a federal judge issued arrest warrants thursday for four 
soldiers implicated in those killings but there have been no 
arrests 
army spokesman lt ricardo mendoza said the military had no 
information on the latest incident in the village of tres ceibas 
11 miles north of san salvador 
alfonso ayala a judiciary official at the scene called the 
killings executions 
uniformed men took away and killed my son they said they were 
from the 1st army brigade said mario chavarria flores the 
father of cornelio marroquin 25 
in addition to cornelio marroquin relatives said the dead 
included oscar marroquin 19 pedro marroquin 20 and gertrudis 
rivera 25 the three marroquins are distant relatives 
the relatives said the four were not partisans of either side in 
the 9year civil war which has claimed an estimated 65000 lives 
the relatives said several men in army uniforms came to this 
isolated hamlet at about 10 pm friday 
the men knocked on the doors of several houses asking for 
people by name the villagers said the four they found were then 
bound by the thumbs and marched off the relatives said 
minutes later the relatives heard gunshots 
they found the bodies laid in a row about 30 yards from the 
homes all had been shot in the head 
chavarria said he tried to follow when the men took away his 
son but they shot over my head and told me to look for him 
tomorrow saturday at the 1st brigade 
i felt so powerless but they had their guns pointed at me 
and what could i do said chavarria his face lined with tears 
in the sept 21 incident in san francisco in san vicente 
province the killers wore jiboa battalion insignia and were 
readily identified as such by dozens of witnesses the army 
acknowledged jiboa soldiers were operating in the village the day 
of the killings 
rebels sometimes kill civilians suspected of collaborating with 
the armed forces but they usually claim responsibility for such 
