<DOCNO> AP881015-0179 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a soontobe released product called the cboe 250 is so eagerly 
anticipated that its introduction has been delayed to make sure 
everyone who wants it can get it 
no its not a car or a computer its a new stockindex 
futures contract the first to be approved by federal regulators 
since last years stockmarket collapse 
its also the first futures contract that will trade on the 
floor of the chicago board options exchange and the first major 
offering of a joint venture between the cboe and the chicago board 
of trade the worlds largest futures market 
the board of trade and the cboe the worlds largest options 
exchange expected about 200 of their members to sign up to trade 
cboe 250 futures instead more than 500 people have expressed 
their intention to participate in the market forcing the exchanges 
to postpone the contracts launch date from nov 1 to nov 11 
this is the first time weve ever put off the launch of a 
contract because of something like this said cbot spokesman ray 
carmichael it could even be that well have to put it off beyond 
the 11th but we still hope to launch it on that date 
the contract is based on the cboe 250 stock index which 
measures the composite performance of the 250 largest stocks traded 
on the new york stock exchange 
the futures contract will allow investors to speculate on the 
indexs performance by committing themselves to buy or sell a 
basket of the underlying stocks for a specified price on a 
specified future date 
the most important feature of the new contract according to 
cboe operations planner william barclay is that it will allow 
players in the cboes popular stock index options markets to hedge 
against losses there thus reducing their risk and the overall risk 
of the markets 
a stockindex option gives the holder an option but not an 
obligation to buy or sell a basket of stocks at a specified price 
on a specified future date 
an investor who has bet via the options market on a rise in 
the stock market could hedge against a loss on that investment by 
selling a cboe 250 futures contract or vice versa 
because futures trading concepts may be unfamiliar to some cboe 
members those who want to trade cboe 250 index futures are 
required to take a futurestrading course and pass a test 
authorized by the commodity futures trading commission the federal 
agency that regulates us futures and options markets 
meanwhile members of the board of trade seeking to participate 
in the new market are not allowed on the cboe floor without first 
attending orientation classes to learn about floor rules peculiar 
to the exchange 
all this processing and training is causing the holdup in 
launching the new contract officials said 
although four other stockindex futures are traded on us 
exchanges with the most successful by far being the chicago 
mercantile exchanges standard amp poors 500 contract the cboe 250 
will be the first launched since the stock markets collapse last 
oct 19 
the crash focused public attention on stockindex futures the 
securities and exchange commission said certain types of 
sophisticated trading activities involving index futures may have 
accelerated the collapse 
a handful of brokerage houses curtailed their involvement in 
those trading activities called program trading and index 
arbitrage in the wake of the publicity that developed 
in index arbitrage traders sell in one market while 
simultaneously buying in another in an attempt to profit from the 
constantly changing prices in both markets one type of program 
trading involves the use of computers for arbitrage trades of huge 
blocks of stocks and stockindex futures contracts 
despite the withdrawal of a few firms from such activities 
analysts say index arbitrage and program trading now play an even 
larger role in the financial markets because many smaller less 
sophisticated investors who fled the markets after the crash have 
not returned 
the cboe 250 index futures will likely become just one more 
avenue for arbitrage said jack barbanel director of futures 
trading with gruntal amp co in new york 
the only benefit i can see of that contract is that it 
provides some interesting arbitrage opportunities between cboe 
options and the futures contract he said it will enable you 
to use a combination of hedging and arbitrage strategies and that 
is really its greatest marketing advantage 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

